---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <style>
      :root{
        --bg:#0b0f1a; --ink:#f5f6ff; --muted:#b9c3e0; --accent:#a7e0ff; --accent2:#ffd166;
        --panel:#11162a; --edge:#222b4f; --glow: 0 0 24px rgba(167,224,255,.35);
      }
      html,body{height:100%}
      body{
        margin:0; font:16px/1.6 ui-rounded, system-ui, Segoe UI, Roboto, Ubuntu;
        color:var(--ink);
        background:
          url('/Mountains.png') no-repeat center center fixed,
          radial-gradient(1000px 600px at 15% -10%, rgba(21,34,75,0.8) 0%, var(--bg) 60%),
          radial-gradient(900px 700px at 90% 10%, rgba(27,34,65,0.8) 0%, transparent 60%),
          linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(11,15,26,0.8),rgba(11,15,26,0.8));
        background-size: cover;
      }
      header.site{
        position:sticky;top:0;z-index:5;
        background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.88);
        color: #000;
        backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.08);
      }
      main{max-width:1400px;margin:0 auto;padding:28px}

      .hero{
        margin-top:12px; display:grid; gap:26px; grid-template-columns:1fr; align-items:center;
        text-align:center;
      }
      .title{margin:0;font-size:52px;line-height:1.1;letter-spacing:.4px;color:#fff}
      .subtitle{margin:.6rem 0 0;color:#fff;font-size:20px}

      /* panels below */
      .section{margin:32px 0}
      .section h2{margin:.2rem 0 .6rem;font-size:28px;color:#fff}
      .grid{display:grid;gap:14px}
      .card{background:linear-gradient(180deg,#101632,#0c122a);border:1px solid var(--edge);border-radius:16px;padding:16px;color:var(--ink);box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,.35)}
      .card h3{margin:.2rem 0 .2rem;color:#fff}
      .card p{margin:.2rem 0 0;color:var(--muted)}
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site"><Header /></header>
    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div>
          <h1 class="title">Adventurers, welcome to the Table</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">Campaign portals, session notes, and worlds—explore at your leisure.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Active Campaigns</h2>
        <div class="grid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr))">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Acroterra</h3>
            <p>Welcome to Acroterra
Acroterra is my homebrew world—a living, breathing land of ancient creation myths, divine conflict, and cultures shaped by both wonder and war. Here, you’ll find towering mountain fortresses, floating forests, haunted wastelands, and seas guarded by secrets older than the continents themselves.

You can expect:

Mythic Origins – A pantheon of powerful deities forged the world, each leaving their mark in the lands, races, and magic of Acroterra. Their rivalries and alliances shaped history—and still ripple through the present.

Races Unique to the World – From the forest-guarding Elvenkin and beast-bonded guardians, to the proud Dragonkin descended from legendary half-dragons, Acroterra is home to peoples not found in traditional 5E, with rich cultures and tangled histories.

Three Vast Continents –

Zoria, the melting pot, scarred by war but thriving in peace—at least on the surface.

Neucrela, a land of human empires, undead strongholds, and an unending struggle for dominance.

Avrela, tense with racial divides, dotted with lands “touched by the gods,” and alive with wonders both beautiful and perilous.

Ancient Conflicts – The War of Eternal Night pitted gods, mortals, and dragons against one another, leaving scars in the land and echoes in modern politics.

Magic, Monsters, and Mystery – Hidden cities of vampires, forests that twist into labyrinths, storms blessed by tempest deities, and artifacts whispered to be lost since the dawn of creation.

Whether you seek high heroics, political intrigue, or dangerous expeditions into lands where mortals were never meant to tread, Acroterra offers stories waiting to be forged. The road will be long, the dangers real—but the legends you make here may last forever.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Coming Soon</h3>
            <p>New realms appear as the weave shivers. Watch this space for fresh adventures.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Table Rules</h2>
        <div class="card">
          <ul style="margin:0 0 0 1rem;color:var(--muted")>
            <li>Be excellent to each other.</li>
            <li>Have fun, lift your party, share the spotlight.</li>
            <li>Safety tools welcome—speak up and we’ll adjust.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
